  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How I make a call in Jio sim?",
  "response": "Making a call using a Jio SIM is straightforward, just like with any other SIM card. Here\u2019s how you can do it:\n\n### **Steps to Make a Call Using Jio SIM:**\n1. **Insert the Jio SIM**: Ensure your Jio SIM is properly inserted into your phone\u2019s SIM card slot.\n2. **Check Network Signal**: Make sure you have a strong Jio network signal (4G/LTE). If there\u2019s no signal, restart your phone or check your SIM settings.\n3. **Enable Mobile Data**: Jio calls use VoLTE (Voice over LTE), so ensure your mobile data is turned on. Go to **Settings** > **Mobile Data** and turn it on.\n4. **Dial the Number**: Open your phone\u2019s dialer (Phone app) and enter the phone number you want to call.\n5. **Make the Call**: Tap the call button to initiate the call. Since Jio uses VoLTE, the call will be made over the 4G network.\n6. **End the Call**: Once done, tap the red end-call button to disconnect.\n\n### **Enable VoLTE (if not enabled):**\nIf you\u2019re unable to make or receive calls, check if VoLTE is enabled:\n   - Go to **Settings** > **Mobile Networks** > **VoLTE Calling** and toggle it on.\n   - If you don\u2019t see this option, contact Jio customer care or visit a Jio store for assistance.\n\n### **Using Jio SIM in a Non-VoLTE Phone:**\nIf your phone does not support VoLTE, you can use the **Jio4GVoice App** to make calls:\n   1. Download and install the **Jio4GVoice App** from the Google Play Store or Apple App Store.\n   2. Open the app and log in with your Jio number.\n   3. Use the in-app dialer to make calls.\n\n### **Check Balance and Validity:**\nEnsure your Jio SIM is active and has sufficient balance or validity for outgoing calls. You can check your balance by:\n   - Dialing **\\*333#** or **\\*555#**.\n   - Using the **MyJio App**.\n\n### **Contact Jio Customer Care:**\nIf you\u2019re still unable to make calls, contact Jio customer care at **198** or **199** for assistance.\n\nLet me know if you need further help! \ud83d\ude0a",
  "temperature": 1.0,
